{"questionId":"9074609","questionHtml":"<p>Two cylinders, X and Y, made from the same material, are connected in series.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ff97d4c165e12cc201eb8158c212f0f363987bfa.png\"></p>\n<p>The cross-sectional area of Y is twice that of X. The drift speed of the electrons in X is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub></math> and&nbsp;in Y it is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is the ratio <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; 4</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; 2</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; 1</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074609","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.22","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two cylinders, X and Y, made from the same material, are connected in series. The cross-sectional area of Y is twice that of X. The drift speed of the electrons in X is vX and in Y","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}